	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p>I have a large business acquaintance<lb/> in <placeName>New York</placeName> but none to avail me in this<lb/> respect.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Such excursions would not be<lb/> requisite forms did we not mean to<lb/> adhere to faith otherwise both gold<lb/> &#38; beauty would be within our reach.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Though rather a delicate matter<lb/> I am writing about I am encouraged<lb/> to do so by confidence in you as a<lb/> gentleman &#38; that no unworthy use<lb/> will be made of.</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Joseph S Freedman</persName></p>
				<p>N. B.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Have you recd. the draft for those<lb/> books&#63;  please acknowledge recpt.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the bottom of the page."><date>6&#45;7&#45;1853</date></p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Detroit</placeName> <date>June 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">For account<lb/> of <persName>Mr Bressler</persName> I enclose &#36;3 as soon<lb/> as those books are disposed of I shall<lb/> make returns.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">In <sic>adressing</sic> the following<lb/> few lines to you concerning a private<lb/> affair I hope you will excuse my<lb/> trespassing upon your time and to be<lb/> brief I will be plain.  Would you<lb/> have the kindness in case I should<lb/> during the course of the <sic>sumer</sic> visit<lb/> <placeName>Philada.</placeName> of introducing me to some Jewish<lb/> families of respectability &#38; worth&#63;<lb/> My object is not business but to form<lb/> another connection.  Could you intro&#45;<lb/>duce me to some that are Americans<lb/> by birth &#38; education or so by manners<lb/> and language&#63;  It seems to me<lb/> there must be a large number of Portuguese<lb/> or others of that class in <placeName>Phild.</placeName> than at any<lb/> other place.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the top center of the page."><persName role="author">Joseph Freedman</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the top right of the page."><persName>Leeser</persName> </p>
				<p rend="The following is written at the bottom of the page."><date>6&#45;7&#45;1853</date></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Penn</hi></placeName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways."><persName>A Ellen Cozens</persName> <lb/> <persName>Detra Cozens</persName><lb/> <persName>Leeser Cozens</persName><lb/> <persName>Samuel Cozens</persName><lb/> <add>&#63;</add></p>
